doc:lib.member.doc:lib.name: Syntelos.add
doc:lib.member.doc:desc: Add a function (or any non null value) to the community library, and define its properties 'canonicalName', 'localName', 'collectionName' and 'collectionLeaf'. Update the 'collectionLeaf' property of the container of the 'fconst' object to value 'false'.

doc:param.doc:desc: The dotted canonical name for this function or global object, eg, "Syntelos.add".
A function or other object (by reference).

doc:return.doc:desc: Silently returns for success, or throws an exception for a null or missing argument or an extremely weird state preventing success.
